A non-governmental organisation, Asmau Foundation has offered medical care to over two thousand patients in Okene, the headquarters of Okene Local government area of Kogi State during its annual medical outreach. The founder and chairman of the foundation, Alhaji Sanusi Abubakar, who disclosed this to journalists said, eye treatment for cataract, pterygium were carried out while correctional glasses and eye drugs were given to the over two thousand patients at Okene General Hospital. Alhaji Abubakar assured the people that efforts would be made to sustain the medical outreach. ALSO READ: Lassa fever: NULGE urges workers to maintain effective sanitation God saved me from chopper crash ― Osinbajo End cultism or resign, Gov Bello warns heads of tertiary… Group calls for mop up of firearms in Kogi Governor Bello swears in commissioners, appoints 30 new… Speaking also, Alhaji Abdulrahman Adoke, who is the special assistant to the chairman of the foundation, advised the people to always appreciate the good gesture of the Asmau Foundation, noting that this would encourage him to do more. Adoke equally advised those that were not able to benefit from the exercise to exercise patience till the next phase of the programme, which he noted would be coming in December this year. He called on other well-to-do individuals and similar organisations to complement the efforts of the government by extending help to the people. He noted that the government alone cannot meet the needs of the people, hence the need for spirited individuals to help the poor in their communities. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS A